CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 19, 1964, pg. 1, reads: "Meter Maid - Mrs. Willa Chandler, one of the six recently appointed Meter Maids in Pittsburgh, checks one of the parking meters downtown. Motorists had better beware when that red flag goes up, as she just might write one of those dreaded tickets.  She was sworn in, with the others, on Monday. - Harris Photo."It has been stated that she was the first African American parking enforcement officer in Pittsburgh. The car in background is probably a 1964 Ford Galaxie.
TitMainTitle: Portrait of parking enforcement officer ("meter maid") Willa "Kitty" Chandler, checking parking meter in front of Civic Arena
